ber , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Baron Nicholas Willington II was born about 1327, in Willington, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1327–":"umbes 1327–Surnud","1353–1394":"1353–1394","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1327":"1327","about 1327":"umbes 1327","1353":"1353","1394":"1394","Willington,South Derbyshire,Derbyshire,England.":"Willington, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1327–":"noin 1327–Kuollut","1353–1394":"1353–1394","1327–Male":"1327–Kuollut","1327":"1327","about 1327":"noin 1327","1353":"1353","1394":"1394","Willington,South Derbyshire,Derbyshire,England.":"Willington, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1327–":"environ 1327–Décédé","1353–1394":"1353–1394","1327–Male":"1327–Décédé","1327":"1327","about 1327":"environ 1327","1353":"1353","1394":"1394","Willington,South Derbyshire,Derbyshire,England.":"Willington, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Baron Nicholas Willington II est né environ 1327, à Willington, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1327–":"um 1327–Verstorben","1353–1394":"1353–1394","1327–Male":"1327–Verstorben","1327":"1327","about 1327":"um 1327","1353":"1353","1394":"1394","Willington,South Derbyshire,Derbyshire,England.":"Willington, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Baron Nicholas Willington II wurde um 1327 in Willington, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1327–":"about 1327–Desede","1353–1394":"1353–1394","1327–Male":"1327–Desede",